P(R \cap S) = P(R)\times P(S) = (0.1)\times(0.15) = 0.015 = 1.5\%
P(\bar{R}\cap \bar S) = (1 - 0.1)\times (1 - 0.15) = (0.9)\times(0.85) = 0.765 = 76.5\%
(\dagger)
 \begin{align} \Pr(\text{rain or snow (or both)}) & = 1 - \Pr(\text{neither rain nor snow}) \\[10pt] & = 1 - \Pr(\text{not rain AND not snow}) \\[10pt] & = 1 - \Pr(\text{not rain})\cdot\Pr(\text{ not snow}). \end{align} 
